Initial settings: Add a User, Network Settings, Configure Services, display the list of services which are running,
                    Stop and turn OFF auto-start setting for a service if you donâ€™t need it, Sudo Settings.
                    
Steps: 

1. Add a User in a kali linux: adduser <username>
2. Network Setting In Kali Linux IP Address Command: ifconfig
3. Configure Services In Kali Linux: service <service_name> start
4. To display the list of services which are running In Kali Linux: sudo systemctl -t=service --state=running
5. To start service: sudo systemctl start <service_name>
6. To stop service: sudo systemctl stop <service_name>
7. To enable service: sudo systemctl enable <service_name>
